cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.RO 

This paper is about semantic labeling for very high resolution images using a deep model with convolutional neural networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel deep model, which involves training the network to improve labeling coherence and accuracy, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves the use of multi-scale contexts and residual correction, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning and deep learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The paper also involves the use of remote sensing applications, which falls under the category of cs.GR (Graphics) and cs.RO (Robotics).
